A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Courts – Global Warming and Climate Change – Prohibited Actions
3 (Ratepayer Protection Act of 2025)
4 FOR the purpose of prohibiting the State or a local government, or an agency of the State
5 or a local government, from filing certain actions against a business for the adverse
6 effects of global warming or climate change in the State; and generally relating to
7 prohibiting the filing of certain actions related to global warming and climate
8 change.
9 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
10 Article – Commercial Law
11 Section 14–3501(a) and (b)
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2013 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
14 BY adding to
15 Article – Courts and Judicial Proceedings
16 Section 5–428
17 Annotated Code of Maryland
18 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
19 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
20 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
21 Article – Commercial Law
22 14–3501.
