2 HOUSE BILL 903
1 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
2 (b) (1) “Business” means a sole proprietorship, partnership, corporation,
3 association, or any other business entity, whether or not organized to operate at a profit.
4 (2) “Business” includes a financial institution organized, chartered,
5 licensed, or otherwise authorized under the laws of this State, any other state, the United
6 States, or any other country, and the parent or subsidiary of a financial institution.
7 Article – Courts and Judicial Proceedings
8 5–428.
9 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
10 INDICATED.
11 (2) “BUSINESS” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 14–3501 OF THE
12 COMMERCIAL LAW ARTICLE.
13 (3) “CLIMATE CHANGE” MEANS THE INCREASING CHANGES IN THE
14 MEASURES OF CLIMATE OVER A LONG PERIOD OF TIME, INCLUDING PRECIPITATION,
15 TEMPERATURE, AND WIND PATTERNS.
16 (4) “GLOBAL WARMING” MEANS THE RISE IN GLOBAL
17 TEMPERATURES DUE TO THE INCREASING CONCENTRATIONS OF GREENHOUSE
18 GASES IN THE ATMOSPHERE.
19 (B) THIS SECTION DOES NOT:
20 (1) PROHIBIT THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT, THE STATE, OR A LOCAL
21 GOVERNMENT FROM ENFORCING HEALTH, ENVIRONMENTAL, ZONING, OR ANY
22 OTHER APPLICABLE LAW; OR
23 (2) RELIEVE A BUSINESS FROM THE RESPONSIBILITY OF COMPLYING
24 WITH THE TERMS OF ANY APPLICABLE FEDERAL, STATE, OR LOCAL LAW.
25 (C) THE STATE OR A LOCAL GOVERNMENT, OR AN AGENCY OF THE STATE
26 OR A LOCAL GOVERNMENT, MAY NOT FILE AN ACTION FOR MONETARY DAMAGES OR
27 ALLEGED ECONOMIC DAMAGES AGAINST A BUSINESS FOR THE ADVERSE EFFECTS OF
28 GLOBAL WARMING OR CLIMATE CHANGE IN THE STATE.
29 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
30 October 1, 2025.

